article.headline: TCU 60, SMU 53
article.story: DALLAS -- Edvinas Ruzgas scored 22 points as TCU rallied in the second half to defeat SMU 60-53 Wednesday night. Zvonko Buljan (nine rebounds) and Ronnie Moss each added 14 points for the Horned Frogs (5-3), who started the second half with a 23-6 run to overcome a 28-23 halftime deficit. Papa Dia and Derek Williams led the Mustangs (2-3) with 16 points apiece while Mouhammad Faye recorded his first career double-double with 11 points and 12 rebounds. Ruzgas shot 7 for 10 from the field, including 4 for 5 from 3-point range. He and Moss each scored eight points during TCU's momentum-changing run. After trailing 50-38 with 7:33 left, SMU pulled to within one twice in the final 3:14 but couldn't retake the lead. The Horned Frogs fell behind 8-0 and didn't score until Buljan hit two free throws with 12:23 remaining in the first half.
